==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interpel
<hw>In`ter*pel"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>interpellare</ets>, <ets>interpellatum</ets>; <ets>inter</ets>
between + <ets>pellare</ets> (in comp.), akin to <ets>pellere</ets> to
drive: cf. F. <ets>interpeller</ets>. Cf. <er>Interpellate</er>.]</ety>
<def>To interrupt, break in upon, or intercede with.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am <qex>interpelled</qex> by many businesses.</q>
<rj><qau>Howell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interpellant</ent>⟦br⟧
